HEADWORD: Low-lived
<hw>Low"-lived`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Characteristic of,
or like, one bred in a low and vulgar condition of life; mean;
dishonorable; contemptible; <as>as, <ex>low-lived</ex>
dishonesty</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lowly</ent>⟦br⟧
